{
  "slug": "repairing-cracks-in-air-dry-greenware",
  "title": "Repairing cracks in air-dry clay during drying",
  "subtitle": "Identifying and patching cracks before the clay is fully dry",
  "excerpt": "Cracks in air-dry clay are most repairable before the clay has fully dried. This technique covers identifying drying cracks early, patching with fresh clay and slurry, and slowing the drying rate to prevent recurrence.",
  "type": "TECHNIQUE",
  "categorySlug": "pottery-ceramics",
