  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cracks in "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "greenware"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "greenware"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " appear when different sections of a piece dry at different rates. The faster-drying section shrinks ahead of the slower one, pulling apart at the join. Most drying cracks are preventable; those that do appear are fixable if caught early enough, at "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "leather-hard"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "leather-hard"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " or slightly beyond, while the clay around the crack still contains some moisture."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why cracks happen"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Uneven wall thickness: thin sections dry faster than thick sections, pulling the join apart."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Exposed rims: rims and edges have more surface area and dry faster than the body."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Warm dry air: direct sunlight, nearby radiators, or fans dry the surface before the interior is ready."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Inadequate joining: cracks at joins where score and slip was insufficient."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Repairing at leather-hard"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Identify the crack. Run a fingernail along it; a crack that opens slightly is still damp enough to patch. A crack that feels hard and powdery at the edges is close to bone-dry and harder to repair."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Mix a small amount of fresh clay with water to make a thick slurry, slightly thicker than double cream."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Score both faces of the crack with the needle tool to roughen them."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Press slurry into the crack and over the edges. Press a thin strip of fresh clay over the crack, pressing it firmly into the slurry. Smooth the clay strip with a damp sponge."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cover the repaired area loosely with damp cloth or plastic to slow the drying of the patch relative to the surrounding clay. If the patch dries faster than the surrounding area, it will crack again."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Repairing at bone-dry"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "At "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "bone-dry"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "bone-dry"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", fresh clay will not bond. There is no moisture left for slurry to grip. Add a few drops of water to dampen the area first. Then patch with slurry and fresh clay. You can also fill the crack with PVA glue; this holds the crack but does not restore the full strength."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Preventing recurrence"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "After patching, wrap the piece loosely in plastic and allow to dry slowly over 48 hours at room temperature. Avoid direct sun, open windows, or heating that dries one side faster than another. Repair without prevention only postpones the crack reappearing."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Not scoring the crack before patching. Fresh clay pressed over an unscored surface falls off as it dries."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Drying the patch in open air immediately. The patch dries faster than the surrounding clay and re-cracks."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Patching at bone-dry with clay slurry. Slurry needs moisture in both surfaces to form a bond; bone-dry clay has none."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}